about.summary: Makes working with XML feel like you are working with JSON

name: xmltodict
raw_recipe:
{% set name = "xmltodict" %}
{% set version = "0.10.2" %}
{% set sha256 = "fc518ccf9adbbb917a2ddcb386be852ae6dd36935e1e8b9a3e760201abfdbf77" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  number: 0
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record=record.txt

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools
  run:
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - xmltodict

about:
  home: https://github.com/martinblech/xmltodict
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'Makes working with XML feel like you are working with JSON'
  dev_url: https://github.com/martinblech/xmltodict

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - synapticarbors
